    <text id="A6215T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>Byrd and Sibert direct David Evans to collect money due them from a third
                party.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    <name type="recipient">Mr D. Evans</name>
                </head>

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1868-05-05">May 5th 1868</date>
                        <name type="place">Bridgewater Va</name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>Dear Sir:</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>According to promise we enclose you note on Parkins, Nelson <del rend="none" hand="h1"/> for
                    70$ due 1st April--also an order on Same for 25$ due March 20th.</p>
                <p>Please present again for collection if it is not convenient for them to pay the
                    money, take a negotiable for the <abbr expan="amount">amt</abbr> of the note and
                    order, payable in 20 or 30 Days. Notify us as to the result, and we shall be
                    under many obligations to you for your attention to it.</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>Yours Truly</salute>
                    <signed>Byrd &amp; Sibert<lb/>Dr Sibert</signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
